# Application Configuration
NODE_ENV=development
PORT=3000
SESSION_SECRET=your-super-secret-session-key-here

# Mailgun Email Configuration
# Leave these empty to use mock email service (logs to console)
# Set these values to enable real email notifications via Mailgun

# Mailgun API Configuration
MAILGUN_API_KEY=your-mailgun-api-key-here
MAILGUN_DOMAIN=your-mailgun-domain-here
EMAIL_FROM=noreply@your-domain.com

# Example configurations:

# Mailgun Sandbox (for testing)
# MAILGUN_DOMAIN=sandbox123abc.mailgun.org
# EMAIL_FROM=noreply@sandbox123abc.mailgun.org

# Your Own Domain (for production)
# MAILGUN_DOMAIN=your-domain.com
# EMAIL_FROM=noreply@your-domain.com

# Email Testing Configuration
# All monitor alerts will be sent to efemarko1@gmail.com (configured in emailService.js)

# To get your Mailgun credentials:
# 1. Sign up at https://www.mailgun.com/
# 2. Go to https://app.mailgun.com/app/domains
# 3. Use sandbox domain for testing or add your own domain
# 4. Get your API key from https://app.mailgun.com/app/account/security

# Security Notes:
# - Never commit .env files to version control
# - Use Mailgun sandbox domain for testing
# - Monitor your Mailgun usage and logs
# - Copy this file to .env and fill in your actual values
